documents.review: I always get a half size up in my tennis shoes. For some reason these feel to big in the heel area and wide.

documents.product_description: NIKE Women's Flex Supreme TR 4 Cross Trainer
documents.review: Comfortable shoe.  I would buy again

documents.name: doc_0_1260
documents.product_description: NIKE Women's Flex Supreme TR 4 Cross Trainer
documents.review: It looks a bit nicer on the picture. Its very light in such a way that when I held the box I wondered if there was just paper filling inside. They are comfortable for the most. Good looking training shoes overall.

documents.name: doc_0_306
documents.product_description: NIKE Women's Flex Supreme TR 4 Cross Trainer
documents.review: they are very comfortable feel like you have nothing on.

documents.name: doc_0_2461
documents.product_description: NIKE Women's Flex Supreme TR 4 Cross Trainer
documents.review: Nice fit

documents.name: doc_0_2681
documents.product_description: NIKE Women's Flex Supreme TR 4 Cross Trainer
documents.review: I got a hot spot on the bottom of my foot the first day I wore them.

documents.name: doc_0_497
documents.product_description: NIKE Women's Flex Supreme TR 4 Cross Trainer
documents.review: The picture makes the shoe look like it has a "boxier" toe rather than the "pointier" toe that it actually has. I have wider feet and generally need to buy a size or half size longer to get a comfortable width (in any brand of shoe). I was shooting for a rounder, broader toe design which is more comfortable for me, and I feel that the pictures of this shoe didn't accurately depict what I received, in that one detail. Otherwise, "the shoe fits." So I am wearing it.

documents.name: doc_0_3138
documents.product_description: NIKE Women's Flex Supreme TR 4 Cross Trainer
documents.review: The shoe is too large. When you do lunges it hurts the heel. The shoe size from a local store is the size I ordered from Amazon however the size or fitting seems to be large

documents.name: doc_1_816
documents.product_description: NIKE Women's Flex Supreme TR 4 Cross Trainer
documents.review: Not a fan. Shoes looked great but too narrow for most feet.

documents.name: doc_1_2861
documents.product_description: NIKE Women's Flex Supreme TR 4 Cross Trainer
documents.review: Great shoe, very comfortable

documents.name: doc_1_849
documents.product_description: NIKE Women's Flex Supreme TR 4 Cross Trainer
documents.review: Comfortable and lightweight. Need a good training shoe that's also supportive and flexible.  I really like the fit, but had to get 1/2 size larger as this style in my size is too perfect from heel to toe.

documents.name: doc_1_1877
documents.product_description: NIKE Women's Flex Supreme TR 4 Cross Trainer
documents.review: I actually have 3 pairs of these trainers.  They are very comfortable, there is a neoprene sleeve that goes around your ankle that makes them the most comfortable for me compared to normal athletic shoes.  They run a little narrow - for me this is perfect, but you may want to round up on the size or try on in the store first if your feet are on the wider side.

documents.name: doc_1_314
documents.product_description: NIKE Women's Flex Supreme TR 4 Cross Trainer
documents.review: I have wide feet and these were too narrow but very nice looking.

documents.name: doc_1_399
documents.product_description: NIKE Women's Flex Supreme TR 4 Cross Trainer
documents.review: The lines don't really show up unless there is a bright light on them. But other than that they are perfect. They are very true to size and are comfortable the first time you put them on.

documents.name: doc_1_1390
documents.product_description: NIKE Women's Flex Supreme TR 4 Cross Trainer
documents.review:
I got the impression it's cushiony and comfy by reading the reviews on this product, when i tried it on it was a much firmer than my other work shoes, i'm standing all day and need enough support and comfort, this isn't the right product for that.
So i had to return it, but i would assume it would work fine for training.

It looks decent and clean. and seems sturdy.  just not the right thing for me.
I was refunded instantly upon returning so.. credit for that.
